title: Gumbo Meal Prep
directions: In a skillet, brown sausage. Remove to slice.
In the same skillet, add olive oil, garlic, onions, salt and spices. Saute until lightly browned. Add the sliced sausage back in the pan with the onions.
In a crockpot, add the rest of the ingredients, and then add the sauteed onions and sausage. Slow cook on low for 4-5 hours, or on high for 2-3 hours, until all vegetables are tender.
This spicy stew freezes well for up to 3 months in an airtight container.
